body:
If anyone knows C / the CPython C API and is interested in a self-contained piece, the JSON IO stuff needs some work.

Adding a `DatetimeArray.values` fixes most of the tests, but we don't want that.

https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/f74fc59793ce1f01e1afcdd29bcdf0dceccaf244/pandas/_libs/src/ujson/python/objToJSON.c#L226 is (I think) where most of the work needs to be done.

btw, the following fixes the encoding issue in the error message (at least for py3). `ValueError: � or � are not JSON serializable yet`

```diff
diff --git a/pandas/_libs/src/ujson/python/objToJSON.c b/pandas/_libs/src/ujson/python/objToJSON.c
index a5e936407..77c9ebdba 100644
--- a/pandas/_libs/src/ujson/python/objToJSON.c
+++ b/pandas/_libs/src/ujson/python/objToJSON.c
@@ -279,8 +290,8 @@ static PyObject *get_values(PyObject *obj) {
             repr = PyString_FromString("<unknown dtype>");
         }

-        PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "%s or %s are not JSON serializable yet",
-                     PyString_AS_STRING(repr), PyString_AS_STRING(typeRepr));
+        PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "%R or %R are not JSON serializable yet",
+                     repr, typeRepr);
         Py_DECREF(repr);
         Py_DECREF(typeRepr);
```
